  "course_description": "Provides an introduction to business data analysis using SPSS from IBM. SPSS, which is used by organizations across a wide variety of industries, is a statistical analysis software with point-and-click menus and drag-drop functionality that allows students to quickly learn how to analyze data without requiring programming skills. The course covers key topics such as importing data from Excel, creating new variables, subdividing data, and conducting basic statistical analyses. By the end of the course, students should know to use SPSS for business data analysis projects in coursework, clubs, internships, and future careers.",
